# Dotfiles Navigation

This repository contains various configuration files (dotfiles) for the user's development environment.

## Shell Configuration

The main shell configuration is in [.config/fish/config.fish](mdc:.config/fish/config.fish), which contains:

- Aliases for common commands
- Custom shell functions
- Environment variable configurations
- Path configurations

## Important Aliases

- `dotfiles`: Navigate to the dotfiles repository
- `nsx`: Navigate to the nsx project
- `last`: Navigate to the LaststanceIO project
- `e`: Enhanced directory listing with eza
- `wanip`: Get public IP address

## Custom Functions

The repository includes several custom fish functions for common tasks:

- `save_cursor_config`: Backup Cursor IDE settings
- `rollback_cursor_config`: Restore Cursor IDE settings
- `weather`: Get weather information
- `storage_usage`: Analyze disk usage
- `awsdir`: Switch between AWS profiles

## Development Tools

The configuration includes setup for:

- Node.js via Volta (`$VOLTA_HOME`)
- pnpm package manager
- Python via pyenv
- Docker tools
- Git utilities
